<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta
      name="viewport"
      content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"
    />
    <title>Privacy Policy | OnTask Logistics LLC</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Privacy policy for OnTask Logistics LLC, describing how consultation form information and site usage data are collected, used, and stored."
    />
    <style>
      :root {
        --navy: #0b1530;
        --text-main: #111827;
        --text-muted: #4b5563;
        --bg-body: #f9fafb;
        --border-subtle: #e1e5f0;
      }

      * {
        box-sizing: border-box;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
      }

      html {
        scroll-behavior: smooth;
      }

      body {
        font-family: "Inter", system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,
          "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
        background: var(--bg-body);
        color: var(--text-main);
        line-height: 1.7;
        -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
      }

      main {
        min-height: 100vh;
      }

      .shell {
        max-width: 760px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 64px 20px 96px;
      }

      .page-title {
        font-size: 1.6rem;
        letter-spacing: -0.02em;
        color: var(--navy);
        margin-bottom: 8px;
      }

      .page-intro {
        font-size: 0.94rem;
        color: var(--text-muted);
        margin-bottom: 28px;
        max-width: 40rem;
      }

      .section {
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
        padding-top: 20px;
        margin-top: 20px;
      }

      .section:first-of-type {
        border-top: none;
        padding-top: 0;
        margin-top: 0;
      }

      .section-title {
        font-size: 0.98rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--navy);
        margin-bottom: 8px;
      }

      .section-body {
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        color: var(--text-muted);
      }

      .section-body p + p {
        margin-top: 10px;
      }

      .section-body ul {
        margin-top: 8px;
        padding-left: 18px;
      }

      .section-body li {
        margin-bottom: 4px;
      }

      .footer-note {
        margin-top: 32px;
        font-size: 0.8rem;
        color: var(--text-muted);
      }

      a {
        color: inherit;
        text-decoration: underline;
        text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
        text-underline-offset: 2px;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main>
      <div class="shell">
        <h1 class="page-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="page-intro">
          This Privacy Policy describes how OnTask Logistics LLC collects, uses,
          and stores information submitted through this website. It is intended
          for customers and prospective customers using the route consultation
          form or reviewing service information.
        </p>

        <section class="section" aria-labelledby="info-collected">
          <h2 id="info-collected" class="section-title">
            Information collected through the consultation form
          </h2>
          <div class="section-body">
            <p>
              When you submit a route consultation request, the information you
              provide may include:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Practice or organization name</li>
              <li>Primary contact name and work email address</li>
              <li>Primary county or general service area</li>
              <li>
                Pickup details such as locations, frequency, and the types of
                items moved (for example, specimens or documents)
              </li>
              <li>Any additional context you choose to include in the message</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              Submitting the form is voluntary. However, if required contact or
              route information is omitted, OnTask Logistics LLC may not be able
              to review the request or determine potential route fit.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section" aria-labelledby="info-use">
          <h2 id="info-use" class="section-title">
            How the information is used
          </h2>
          <div class="section-body">
            <p>
              Information submitted through the consultation form is used only
              to:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Review whether your requested service aligns with existing or planned routes</li>
              <li>Contact you to request clarifications or additional details</li>
              <li>
                Provide a response regarding potential route structure, coverage,
                and next steps
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              OnTask Logistics LLC does not sell form submissions or share them
              with third parties for advertising purposes.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section" aria-labelledby="review-storage">
          <h2 id="review-storage" class="section-title">
            How submissions are reviewed and stored
          </h2>
          <div class="section-body">
            <p>
              Consultation submissions are reviewed by OnTask Logistics LLC to
              evaluate route structure, operational fit, and coverage
              availability. Submissions may be retained in email or internal
              records so that future route planning and account discussions can
              reference prior requests.
            </p>
            <p>
              Access to consultation request details is limited to personnel who
              need the information to evaluate service options, schedule
              potential routes, or respond to your inquiry. Information is kept
              for as long as reasonably necessary for these purposes and to meet
              any legal or operational requirements.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section" aria-labelledby="cookies-analytics">
          <h2 id="cookies-analytics" class="section-title">
            Cookies and analytics
          </h2>
          <div class="section-body">
            <p>
              This site may use basic analytics or server logging to understand
              aggregate traffic patterns, such as which pages are visited and
              general time of access. These tools are used to monitor site
              performance and do not intentionally associate browsing activity
              with specific consultation submissions.
            </p>
            <p>
              Your browser may send standard information such as IP address,
              browser type, and referring pages when you visit the site. You can
              adjust your browser settings to control or limit cookies and other
              tracking technologies as needed.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section" aria-labelledby="contact">
          <h2 id="contact" class="section-title">Contact information</h2>
          <div class="section-body">
            <p>
              For questions about this Privacy Policy or how your information is
              handled, you can contact:
            </p>
            <p>
              OnTask Logistics LLC<br />
              Philadelphia, Pennsylvania<br />
              Email:
              <a href="mailto:info@ontask-logistics.com"
                >info@ontask-logistics.com</a
              >
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <p class="footer-note">
          This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. Material
          changes will be reflected by updating the content on this page.
        </p>
      </div>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>

